The paper discusses optimal pricing schemes for social goods, which involves externalities and maximizing revenue. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and mechanism design (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses Bayesian modeling, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on economic concepts such as externalities and pricing, which could fall under the categories of economics and computation (cs.EC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
